Don't let the plastic utensils fool you.  The food was great.  I can only comment on the Caldo de Res (beef soup) since that is all I ordered.  It may ha e been the beat Caldo de Res I've ever tasted. (My mother-in-law's is a close second, but she doesn't read English, so I can be truthful.)   It was spicy and flavorful with a rich broth.  The corn, chayote and string beans were not too soft nor over cooked. I asked for jalapeños on the side, even though the soup is hot.  On the negative side were the store bought tortillas and the long wait for the soup.  At $14 it's not super cheap, but it definitely filled me up.

If disappointment had a face, it'd be that of the Torta de milanesa (Mexican chicken cutlet sandwich) that I ate here.  I decided to order from this place using postmates and was annoyed at the 2+ hour wait time it took to get my meal. Upon calling the restaurant I was met with a man speaking in a tone indicative that he was distraught that I decided to call and ask why my food was not yet ready. On top of having me wait, my patient postmate was also there for too long. He also complained about the restaurant after I received my food.  Now the food, terrible. The torta I had bought, was stiffer than a rock. If I had chosen to throw the sandwich out of my window it may have very well killed any unsuspecting pedestrian that walked by, or broken the concrete sidewalk. I can't believe I didn't chip a tooth after taking that initial bite.  I imagine the cook was mad that I had the audacity to call the restaurant and ask about the progress of my meal.  On top of that I ordered two tacos de Chorizo which were burnt, stiff, cold, and tasted like garbage, because that's essentially what that was.  Worst 55$ purchase of my life thus far, and it sucks because I love food, and I love myself a good torta.  The nachos were surprisingly ok, although they had a weird taste to them which made the "ok" bad.  Overall, spend your money on another Mexican place because this mexican place will only bring you disappointment, and a possible broken tooth.
